@node Main "Bibarr - Documentation"

                              'Bibarr' 1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Bibarr', a @{" Workbench game " link play} that is based on the 'sliding-tile'
type of games, where the goal is to move bars or crosses (which
have two bars) of various colours so they fall in a cross shape
hole that is located at the center of the game board.

  Bars can be moved in two ways: in the direction of the empty
space, or toward a different type of bar, which will combine both
bars to form a cross. If both bars in the cross are of the same
colour, the better it is...

  A peculiarity about the game is that the number of moves made
decreases by 25, any time a cross with two bars of the same colour
fall in the hole... Why not?!

  Have fun!

