@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Bibarr" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Bibarr runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with
      a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To play, click on any bar, cross or small block. In the game,
there are 3 types of shapes that can be moved:

-Simple bar:  This shape can only move in the direction it
              indicates, so a horizontal bar can move horizontally
              and a vertical bar will move vertically. A bar can
              either move toward the empty space or another bar of
              a different type, if it is located next and in line
              with the bar that is to be moved. Another thing is
              that in order to move, the other end of the bar must
              be next to another bar of the same type, a small
              block, a cross or the edge of the game board...

              If a bar moves toward another bar of a different
              type, it will combine with the other bar and form a
              cross. Once together, those bars cannot be separated
              afterwards... The initial position of the bar will
              be replaced by a small octagonal block.

-Cross:       This shape is the result of two bars that have been
              combined together. A cross can only move toward the
              empty space, if it is next to it. Please note that
              it does not matter what shapes are next to a cross.
              If a cross is moved toward the center hole, it will
              fall in the hole and then it will be replaced by a
              small octagonal block.

              Note that when a cross fall in the hole and it has
              two bars of the same colour, the number of moves you
              have made will decrease by 25! ...But the number of
              moves will never be below 1...

-Small block: this octagonal shape can move just about anywhere,
              provided that the empty space is next to it. It
              cannot fall in the center hole, unlike a simple bar
              or a cross. It will just remain 'above' the hole...

  Continue the game until all bars and crosses have fallen in the
center hole, and only small blocks remain...

  If you get stuck in the game, you can click on the 'New Game'
button to start over, but be aware that the amount of moves you
make for the current game is added up until you complete it...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

